### Stack
- Next.js 15+ App Router, TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS 4
- shadcn/ui (slate base) — never edit components/ui/ files by hand
- Lucide React — only icon library
- Framer Motion — always respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Lenis — smooth scroll, wired via SmoothScrollProvider
- React Hook Form + Zod — all forms
- Supabase — database and storage
- Custom auth — argon2id hashing, signed httpOnly cookie sessions, no external auth provider
- pnpm

### File Rules
- One section per file in components/sections/
- All static copy in content/[page].ts as typed const exports; dynamic copy comes from Supabase via lib/db/queries.ts
- Sections never fetch their own data; a Server Component parent fetches and passes props
- Server Components by default; "use client" only for state, effects, or browser APIs
- All mutations go through Server Actions in actions/[entity].ts
- Every mutating Server Action checks session, role, and scope BEFORE writing
- **Dual access control (hierarchy + scope):** every admin mutation must call `getCurrentAdmin()` (or `requireAdmin()` from `lib/auth/access.ts`) first. Then enforce **role level** (higher `roles.level` = more authority) against the action's required minimum — Contributors (20) cannot delete; Editors (50) cannot manage admins, roles, teams, or `site_settings`; only Head Admin (100, `scope = global`) manages those global resources. Separately enforce **team scope** via `getAccessibleScopes(adminId)` / `requireTeamScope()` for team-scoped tables (`pages`, `services`, `visa_subclasses`, `posts`, `team_members`): global roles receive all team IDs; team roles may only mutate rows whose `team_id` is in their scope. Both checks run server-side before any write — never rely on hiding UI.
- All admin mutations must validate CSRF via `assertValidCsrf()` from `lib/auth/csrf.ts`
- Zod schemas in lib/schemas/[entity].ts, shared client and server
- DB helpers in lib/db/queries.ts; components never import the Supabase client directly
- All files live inside the single project root

### Naming
- Files: kebab-case. Components: PascalCase. Functions/vars: camelCase. Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE. Types: PascalCase.
- DB tables: snake_case plural. Columns: snake_case singular.
- Env vars: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE; client-safe ones prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_.
- Routes/slugs: kebab-case.

### Style
- Mobile-first: unprefixed Tailwind targets 375px; md: and lg: scale up.
- All colours via CSS variables, never hardcoded hex outside the token definitions.
- All spacing from the Tailwind scale, no arbitrary values.
- Max two fonts: Playfair Display (display), Source Sans 3 (body).

### Compliance
- Amity is a registered migration agent (MARN 964861), not a law firm. Never claim legal advice, legal representation, or lawyer status.
- Never imply association with "Amity Lawyers" / "Amity Immigration Lawyers" (a separate, unrelated business).
- Footer renders MARN identity from site_settings.compliance_footer.

### Never
- Hardcoded secrets or API keys.
- Secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables.
- Plaintext or reversibly-encrypted passwords.
- Role or scope checks in the UI only; they must run server-side in the Server Action.
- lorem ipsum, purple-to-blue gradients, default Inter font, mixed icon sets.
- Outcome guarantees, success percentages, processing-time promises, or comparative claims in any copy.
- Legal-practice claims or any implied link to Amity Lawyers.
- Banned words: guarantee, guaranteed, risk-free, fast-track, foolproof, stress-free, hassle-free, dream, plus the global list.
- Antigravity or Claude Code; Cursor is the only IDE.

### Supabase
- When creating or modifying Supabase migrations (`supabase/migrations/`), seed data, or schema instructions, **apply them automatically** — do not leave migration application as a manual step for the user.
- Prefer local `supabase db push` / `supabase migration up` when the CLI is linked; otherwise use the Supabase MCP `apply_migration` tool against project `cwecfcjjmcinztzlhtsl`.
- After applying, verify with a read query or `list_migrations` when practical.
